abstract: >-
  Per-trial audit-trail, appendices, and reproducibility runbook for the
  PPAM 2026 paper "LLM-agentic access to a federated scientific data
  layer with Onedata". Contains 1008 trial records from the K=8 headline
  sweep (7 LLMs x 18 scenarios x 8 trials), with as-measured and
  post-clean (rescored + deployment-lifted) oracle outcomes; the seven
  text appendices the PPAM page budget required cutting (server-design
  taxonomy, methodology detail, threats catalogue, scenario verbatim
  briefs, stochasticity decomposition, oracle pseudocode, positioning
  tables); and a reproducibility runbook. The MCP server, harness, and
  rescore tooling are pinned at groundnuty/onedata-mcp@ppam2026/14-tools
  at commit 08e201b.
keywords:
  - Model Context Protocol
  - LLM agents
  - federated scientific data
  - Onedata
  - tool curation
  - execution-based oracle
  - replication package
